g'luck and safe travels <p><Center>Zepf<BR>Level 30 Rogue<BR>Antonius Bayle<BR>"...so stealthy my 'p' is silent..."<BR><BR>Aylias <BR>Level 20 Paladin<BR>Proud member of Frumpkin's Pumpkins on Sullon Zek</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/22/02 1:18:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15354.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Total Noob question about AGI</span><hr size=1> Some stats have other &quot;magic number effects&quot; as well, for example if your STA is 100 or better then you don't suffer the melee stat hits when swinging a heavy weapon a lot.  Your STA bar still goes down, and running and jumping are still affected but your melee stats stay the same so that zing of invigor really isn't necessary. <p><BR>
